# JBIG1 (ITU-T T.82/T.85) Bi-level Image Entity
# Used for fax, scanned documents, and bi-level image compression.
# Extensions: .jbg .jbig .bie (all identical format)
#
# The 20-byte BIH (Bi-level Image Header) has no magic string, making
# reliable detection difficult. This rule checks several header
# constraints to reduce false positives, but may still match other
# binary files. NOT submitted to libmagic for this reason.
#
# Header layout (all multi-byte fields are big-endian):
#   0: DL    (1 byte)  - differential layers, typically 0
#   1: D     (1 byte)  - bit planes, typically 1 (bilevel)
#   2: P     (1 byte)  - horizontal resolution layers
#   3: reserved (1 byte)
#   4: Xd    (4 bytes) - image width
#   8: Yd    (4 bytes) - image height
#  12: L0    (4 bytes) - stripe height
#  16: MX    (1 byte)  - template pixel range
#  17: options (1 byte) - only low 3 bits used
#  18: order (1 byte)  - only low 3 bits used

# DL=0 (no differential layers, most common case)
0	byte		0
# D: number of bit planes, 0 or small number
>1	byte		<9
# horizontal resolution layers, small number
>>2	byte		<8
# width must be positive
>>>4	belong		>0
# height must be positive
>>>>8	belong		>0
# options byte: only bits 0-2 are defined
>>>>>17	byte&0xF8	0
# order byte: only bits 0-2 are defined
>>>>>>18	byte&0xF8	0	JBIG image data,
!:ext	jbg/jbig/bie
>>>>>>>4	belong		x	%d x
>>>>>>>8	belong		x	%d
